info.title: GuildQuality API Documentation
info.description:
GuildQuality offers several methods for retrieving data from and adding data to your GuildQuality account. # Authentication Each request to the API is authenticated by an API bearer token which is unique to each member account. To activate your API credentials, go to Account > API. Once your API credentials have been activated, make sure to keep them guarded. Anyone who has access to them will have access to your survey data as long as the credentials remain active. If you ever need new credentials for any reason, deactivate your current credentials then youâ€™ll be provided with option to request new ones. Credentials are available on the API section of the Settings page of the GuildQuality app. # Error Codes
Status code Meaning
400 Malformed parameters or other bad request.
401 Unauthorized. (Login is required. Check Bearer token is correct.)
422 Unprocessable Entity. (Validation error. Check error message for specific valiation.)
# Rate limit API requests are limited to 300 requests per minute. If requests from a unique IP exceed that limit, then the IP will be blocked for 1 minute.

get.description: Returns child accounts for a given account.
Returns available custom fields and values for an account.

Return affiliate summary review data grouped by company. The following data is returned:

- Company information
- Total number of completed surveys
- Breakdown of review data including average and stars received
- Satisfactory data by question

parameters.name: page
parameters.description:
(Optional) Specify to paginate company reviews 100 companies at a time. A value of 1 will return companies 1 to 100; a value of 2 will return companies 101 to 200; etc. Next, Previous, etc. meta data is also returned.
Format: INT

parameters.description:
(Optional) Specifies the max number of reviews to return
Note: When a limit is specified, the response body will not be paginated
Format: INT

parameters.description:

Format: YYYY-MM-DD
